
open(), openat() access modes:
  O_RDONLY enabled by SCOPE_RPATH
  O_WRONLY enabled by SCOPE_WPATH
  O_RDWR   enabled by (SCOPE_RPATH and SCOPE_WPATH)

  O_CREAT  enabled by SCOPE_CPATH

  other flags that are often set:
  O_APPEND and O_TRUNC: Controlling writing mode
  O_ASYNC: for signal-driven I/O
  O_CLOEXEC: close-on-exec, same permissions as close() (none)
  O_DIRECT: Disable caching (needs O_SYNC)
  O_EXCL: enforce create (needs O_CREAT, so requires SCOPE_CPATH)
